-- Vietnam’s PV Oil Said to Sell Ruby, Chim Sao Crude Shipments
-- B y   R a m s e y   A l - R i k a b i
-- 2012-01-17T09:12:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/vietnam-s-pv-oil-said-to-sell-ruby-chim-sao-crude-shipments.html
PV Oil Co.,  Vietnam ’s state-owned
oil-marketing company, is said to have sold 1 million barrels of
Ruby and Chim Sao crude in four cargoes to  BP (BP/)  Plc,  Royal Dutch
Shell Plc (RDSA) , Chevron and Petroleo Brasileiro SA, said four traders
who participate in the market, declining to be identified
because the information is confidential.  Petroleo Brasileiro, or  Petrobras (PETR4) , and Chevron both bought
Ruby for loading in March at a premium of $6 a barrel to
benchmark Minas prices, the traders said. BP and  Shell (RDSA)  each
bought Chim Sao for February at premiums of as much as $7.80 a
barrel to Dated Brent, they said.  Details of the sales are as follows:  To contact the reporter on this story:
